import requests, json
# find the collection that contains our dataset by searching collections? maybe dataset is in some collection list
# We'll sample first N collections and check if dataset id present.

dsid='21d3e683-80a4-4d9b-bc89-ebb2df513dde'
cols=requests.get('https://api.cellxgene.cziscience.com/dp/v1/collections', timeout=20).json()['collections']
print('num cols', len(cols))
found=[]
for c in cols[:50]:
    cid=c['id']
    detail=requests.get(f'https://api.cellxgene.cziscience.com/dp/v1/collections/{cid}', timeout=20).json()
    if any(d.get('id')==dsid for d in detail.get('datasets',[])):
        found.append(cid)
        break
print('found', found)
